What you need to know:

WRA says water levels in all the five lakes in the Rift Valley have risen to the highest recorded levels in recent years.The main gate to Lake Nakuru has been completely submerged, with the KWS urging tourists to access Lake Nakuru National Park through Lanet and Nderit gates.Lake Baringo has expanded from 236 square kilometres in 2015 to about 270km square, posing a threat to adjacent homesteads and institutions.